[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    120[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## AWS SDK Accuracy
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    121[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    122[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **`s3_client.get_object(Bucket, Key)`:** Correct parameter names. Response parsed via `response["Body"].read()`. ✓
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    123[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **`s3_client.put_object(Bucket, Key, Body, ContentType, ServerSideEncryption)`:** All parameters correct. `ServerSideEncryption="aws:kms"` is the correct value for SSE-KMS. ✓
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    124[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **No `KMSMasterKeyId` specified:** When `ServerSideEncryption="aws:kms"` is used without `SSEKMSKeyId`, S3 uses the AWS-managed key (`aws/s3`). This is fine for a teaching example. Production would use a CMK, as noted in the Gap to Production section. ✓
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    125[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **boto3 `Config(retries=...)`:** Correct usage with `max_attempts` and `mode` keys. ✓
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    126[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **S3 key format:** No leading slashes. ✓
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    127[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **No DynamoDB usage:** The code doesn't use DynamoDB (constraints are in S3 JSON files), so no Decimal/float issue applies. ✓
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    128[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    129[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
